definition.value: An organosulfate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the sulfo groups of dextran sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl fluoride that is fluoroethane carrying an oxo group at position 1.

A pyranoxanthene that is 3,5-dihydro-2H-pyrano[4,3,2-kl]xanthene substituted by methyl groups at positions 2R, 3S, 4, and 10, by an oxo group at position 5, by hydroxy groups at positions 8 and 10, and by a (2S,3S)-3-hydroxybutan-2-yl group at position 9. It is a natural product isolated from the fungus Penicillium citrinum B-57.
A furopyranoxanthene with formula C24H28O6. It is a natural product isolated from the fungus Penicillium citrinum B-57.
An organic heteropentacyclic compound having a skeleton comprising of pyranoxanthene ortho-fused to a furan ring.

A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with an alpha-D-Man-(1->6)-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a (1->4)-linkage and alpha-L-Fuc residues attached via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.
A C27-steroid that is cholesterol carrying a hydroxy group at position 16S and 22S.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of ponatinib resulting from the protonation of the piperazine nitrogen. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

The hydrochloride salt of ponatinib. It is a potent pan inhibitor of tyrosine kinases, active in all single resistance ABL kinase mutations including the T315l mutation. It is approved for the treatment of chronic myeloid leukemia.
A C27-steroid that is cholesterol carrying a hydroxy group at position 16S and an oxo group at position 22.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-glutamic acid, L-arginine, glycine, and L-methionine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A pentapeptide composed of L-glutamic acid, L-arginine, glycine, L-methionine, and L-threonine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A 3beta-hydroxy-Delta(5)-steroid that is furostan carrying a double bond between positions 5-6 and hydroxy groups at positions 3beta and 22R.
An acrylate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of dodecan-1-ol with the carboxy group of acrylic acid.

A branched amino heptasaccharide that is beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 of the mannosyl residue have been glycosylated by a beta-D-xylopyranosyl residue and an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucopyranosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannopyranosyl group respectively, while the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries also an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached via a (1->3)-linkage.
